 x \in \mathbb{Q} \implies \lim_{h \to 0} \frac{1_\mathbb{Q}(x+h) - 1_\mathbb{Q}(x-h)}{2h} = \lim_{h \to 0} \frac{0}{2h} = \lim_{h \to 0} 0 = 0.
